{{zh-forms|[[东隅]]|[[東]][[隅]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
Literally: the eastern corner
:Used as a metaphor to describe the spot where the sun comes out; morning.
* ''c.'' '''398 - 445:''' Fan Ye ([[zh:w:范晔|范瞱]], ''[[w:Book of Later Han|Book of Later Han]], Scroll 17, The Biography of Feng Yi'' ([[zh:source:後漢書]]˙卷十七˙馮異傳)
*: [[可謂]][[失]][[之]]'''東隅'''，[[收]][[之]][[桑榆]]
*:: ''It may be said that if one looses it in the '''morning''', one gains it (back) at sunset.''
===Noun===
{{cmn-noun|t|pin=dōngyú|pint=dong1yu2|tra=東隅|sim=东隅|rs=木04}}
# [[morning]]; [[daybreak]]
# eastern side (of a room)

